I got the same error and I can reproduce it easy:

---


class b;

class a : public b
{
	public:
		a( templ<int> &, s2::classX & );
};

a::a( templ<int> &param1, s2::classX &s2 ) : b(s2) 
{
}

---

* first parameter of the constructor must be a template.
* second parameter type is inside a namespace and the parameter name is called like the namespace itself.
* call super constructor with the 2nd parameter name.

I hope that helps you to fix at least one of these errors

good luck
